1
00:00:04,466 --> 00:00:06,433
[♪]

2
00:01:12,497 --> 00:01:14,664
[ALL GASPING]

3
00:01:19,311 --> 00:01:21,378
MAN:
Wait!

4
00:01:21,411 --> 00:01:23,178
Your Highness,
please!

5
00:01:23,211 --> 00:01:25,111
Wait!

6
00:01:25,144 --> 00:01:27,144
Your Highness.

7
00:01:27,178 --> 00:01:28,478
Really, Omar,

8
00:01:28,511 --> 00:01:30,578
I don't see why you have
to follow me everywhere.

9
00:01:30,611 --> 00:01:32,811
We've been in Metro City
for three days,

10
00:01:32,844 --> 00:01:34,744
and I'm perfectly capable
of finding my way around

11
00:01:34,778 --> 00:01:36,344
without your help.

12
00:01:36,378 --> 00:01:38,644
B-but, Your Highness,
it's for your own safety!

13
00:01:38,678 --> 00:01:41,378
You're not just the average
princess next door.

14
00:01:41,411 --> 00:01:43,611
You're the guardian
of the sacred Scale of Tohron,

15
00:01:43,644 --> 00:01:46,311
the very soul
of our kingdom!

16
00:01:46,344 --> 00:01:47,711
I shudder to think
what would happen

17
00:01:47,744 --> 00:01:49,644
if someone were
to steal it!

18
00:01:49,678 --> 00:01:52,678
Oh, Omar, you're such
an old fusspot.

19
00:01:52,711 --> 00:01:55,878
The scale isn't valuable
to anyone but us or our people.

20
00:01:55,911 --> 00:01:58,878
Here in Metro City,
I just look over-accessorized.

21
00:01:58,911 --> 00:02:02,178
Can't we forget the scale and
just enjoy ourselves for once?

22
00:02:02,211 --> 00:02:04,744
Oh, you're impossible!

23
00:02:04,778 --> 00:02:08,711
I just want to have some fun.
And I'm going to. By myself!

24
00:02:08,744 --> 00:02:10,511
Arrggh! Your Highness!

25
00:02:10,544 --> 00:02:12,411
Wait!
Please, come back!

26
00:02:12,444 --> 00:02:15,144
Your Highness!

27
00:02:19,278 --> 00:02:22,278
Well, you can't get away now,
princess!

28
00:02:22,311 --> 00:02:24,344
Huh?
Where'd she go?

29
00:02:24,378 --> 00:02:26,211
Oh!
[ENGINE RUMBLES]

30
00:02:26,244 --> 00:02:29,544
Whoa!
Princess!

31
00:02:29,578 --> 00:02:31,811
Bon voyage.
Have a safe flight!

32
00:02:31,844 --> 00:02:35,311
Your Highness!

33
00:02:35,344 --> 00:02:37,378
[GIGGLING]

34
00:02:39,811 --> 00:02:43,511
Lord Zaide, Princess Abby
is now unguarded.

35
00:02:43,544 --> 00:02:45,444
ZAIDE:
Good. You know what to do.

36
00:02:45,478 --> 00:02:48,344
Just make sure no one sees you.

37
00:02:49,478 --> 00:02:50,844
Goodbye, princess.

38
00:02:50,878 --> 00:02:53,278
Soon your kingdom will be mine.

39
00:02:57,311 --> 00:02:58,844
ROBOT:
It was very embarrassing.

40
00:02:58,878 --> 00:03:01,278
In the middle of delivering
a singing telegram,

41
00:03:01,311 --> 00:03:03,111
my head fell off.

42
00:03:03,144 --> 00:03:04,778
Sorry I'm always coming to you
for repairs.

43
00:03:04,811 --> 00:03:07,478
Hey, don't sweat it.
Sing "Aah."

44
00:03:07,511 --> 00:03:09,144
♪ Aah ♪
Good.

45
00:03:09,178 --> 00:03:10,244
Perfect.

46
00:03:10,278 --> 00:03:12,444
Thanks, Reno.

47
00:03:12,478 --> 00:03:15,844
♪ Call me, Jody the Robot
When you need a message sung ♪

48
00:03:15,878 --> 00:03:18,411
♪ I'll sing it in Croatian
Or in your native tongue ♪

49
00:03:18,444 --> 00:03:19,544
Out of
my way!

50
00:03:19,578 --> 00:03:21,678
It's Zaide's men!

51
00:03:21,711 --> 00:03:24,144
She's spotted us!
Don't let her get away!

52
00:03:32,178 --> 00:03:33,178
Arrgggh!

53
00:03:33,211 --> 00:03:36,144
Up here!

54
00:03:36,178 --> 00:03:38,178
Follow me!

55
00:03:42,511 --> 00:03:44,311
I wonder
where Reno is.

56
00:03:44,344 --> 00:03:45,611
He better
show up!

57
00:03:45,644 --> 00:03:48,778
Rule 12 is everyone helps
clean the secret hideout!

58
00:03:48,811 --> 00:03:50,444
[RUMBLING]
ALL: Huh?

59
00:03:54,278 --> 00:03:55,878
Reno,
what's happening?

60
00:03:55,911 --> 00:03:58,144
Shh! Some goons
are after us.

61
00:03:58,178 --> 00:03:59,644
Goons?

62
00:03:59,678 --> 00:04:01,678
Did you see the princess?
No.

63
00:04:01,711 --> 00:04:03,178
BOYS:
Princess?

64
00:04:03,211 --> 00:04:04,644
Huh?

65
00:04:04,678 --> 00:04:06,478
She couldn't
have gone far.

66
00:04:06,511 --> 00:04:08,678
Split up
and find her. Go!

67
00:04:10,611 --> 00:04:13,144
Well, it looks like
they've left.

68
00:04:13,178 --> 00:04:16,144
It's okay. You'll
be safe here with us.

69
00:04:16,178 --> 00:04:17,778
Thank you for rescuing me.

70
00:04:17,811 --> 00:04:20,144
Oh, I'm so sorry.

71
00:04:20,178 --> 00:04:22,878
I seem to have made
a new door...in your roof.

72
00:04:22,911 --> 00:04:24,811
Ah, don't worry
about it!

73
00:04:24,844 --> 00:04:26,444
Astro can fix it!

74
00:04:26,478 --> 00:04:28,378
He's got lasers
in his fingers

75
00:04:28,411 --> 00:04:30,811
and a jackhammer in his nose,
or something.

76
00:04:30,844 --> 00:04:33,844
So just who were those guys
in the suits, anyway?

77
00:04:33,878 --> 00:04:36,878
Yeah, and how come they were
chasing after you, princess?

78
00:04:36,911 --> 00:04:38,711
Those were Zaide's men.

79
00:04:38,744 --> 00:04:42,211
Zaide is next in line behind me
to inherit the throne of Mayura.

80
00:04:42,244 --> 00:04:44,144
They're after
the Scale of Tohron.

81
00:04:44,178 --> 00:04:46,844
And they won't stop until
they get their hands on it.

82
00:04:46,878 --> 00:04:49,844
Then you really are
a real live princess?

83
00:04:49,878 --> 00:04:51,844
Yes, I'm Abby.

84
00:04:51,878 --> 00:04:54,878
Uh, what's the Scale of Tohron?

85
00:04:54,911 --> 00:04:57,344
Tohron's the guardian spirit
of Mayura.

86
00:04:57,378 --> 00:04:58,611
He's a mythical dragon.

87
00:04:58,644 --> 00:05:00,578
BOYS:
A dragon? Cool!

88
00:05:02,211 --> 00:05:04,444
Yes.

89
00:05:04,478 --> 00:05:07,144
<i>Long ago, a volcano</i>
<i>threatened our kingdom.</i>

90
00:05:07,178 --> 00:05:09,811
<i>The brave dragon Tohron flew</i>
<i>into the heart of the mountain</i>

91
00:05:09,844 --> 00:05:11,611
<i>to quench its fire.</i>

92
00:05:11,644 --> 00:05:14,811
As he vanished, it is said that
<i>one of his scales fell off,</i>

93
00:05:14,844 --> 00:05:17,311
<i>the Scale of Tohron.</i>

94
00:05:17,344 --> 00:05:19,878
<i>It's been passed down</i>
<i>generation after generation</i>

95
00:05:19,911 --> 00:05:22,778
to a member of the royal family
<i>who serves Tohron</i>

96
00:05:22,811 --> 00:05:25,578
<i>and who will inherit</i>
<i>the throne.</i>

97
00:05:27,444 --> 00:05:30,244
The Scale is the sacred symbol
of the kingdom.

98
00:05:30,278 --> 00:05:32,111
If Zaide were
to take it from me,

99
00:05:32,144 --> 00:05:34,644
then he would be next in line
to become our ruler.

100
00:05:34,678 --> 00:05:38,211
It would put my father,
the king, in great danger.

101
00:05:38,244 --> 00:05:39,678
Zaide hates him.

102
00:05:39,711 --> 00:05:40,811
Well, how come?

103
00:05:40,844 --> 00:05:44,244
Because he is the one
who brought robots into Mayura.

104
00:05:44,278 --> 00:05:46,778
Cool!
Mayura has robots!

105
00:05:46,811 --> 00:05:51,378
Yes. They help us maintain
the ecosystem of our forests.

106
00:05:51,411 --> 00:05:53,111
<i>But Zaide doesn't trust them.</i>

107
00:05:53,144 --> 00:05:56,378
<i>He says they are all</i>
<i>vile, unnatural machines.</i>

108
00:05:56,411 --> 00:05:59,744
If he were king,
he would destroy every robot.

109
00:05:59,778 --> 00:06:01,278
I came here

110
00:06:01,311 --> 00:06:03,844
to see how people and robots
live and work together.

111
00:06:03,878 --> 00:06:08,144
But Omar, my guardian,
is afraid to let me go anywhere.

112
00:06:08,178 --> 00:06:11,478
From the look of those thugs,
I'd say he's got good reason.

113
00:06:11,511 --> 00:06:13,144
Yes, I suppose.

114
00:06:13,178 --> 00:06:14,811
Hey, we'll show you around!

115
00:06:14,844 --> 00:06:16,144
We could be your bodyguards!

116
00:06:16,178 --> 00:06:18,178
Ha, ha, ha. Oh?

117
00:06:18,211 --> 00:06:19,311
And Astro's
on our side!

118
00:06:19,344 --> 00:06:21,178
Mm-hm.

119
00:06:21,211 --> 00:06:23,178
But your disguise does
kind of have "runaway princess"

120
00:06:23,211 --> 00:06:25,178
written
all over it.

121
00:06:25,211 --> 00:06:27,344
All right!
Excellent!

122
00:06:27,378 --> 00:06:29,111
Come on, Abby!
Come on!

123
00:06:29,144 --> 00:06:31,378
[LAUGHING]

124
00:06:31,411 --> 00:06:34,411
RENO:
Hey! Wait up!

125
00:06:34,444 --> 00:06:37,378
Why do I have to wear
a disguise?

126
00:06:37,411 --> 00:06:39,144
Because they saw
your face too.

127
00:06:39,178 --> 00:06:40,378
[BOTH LAUGHING]

128
00:06:40,411 --> 00:06:42,144
So we don't got to
look at you!

129
00:06:42,178 --> 00:06:44,244
This isn't happening.

130
00:06:44,278 --> 00:06:46,611
Abby, come here.
Look.

131
00:06:46,644 --> 00:06:47,678
ABBY:
Wow!

132
00:06:47,711 --> 00:06:50,111
ASTRO:
That's Metro City Square.

133
00:06:51,211 --> 00:06:53,644
Ahhhh!

134
00:06:53,678 --> 00:06:55,578
Caramels? Licorice?
Gumdroids?

135
00:06:55,611 --> 00:06:57,611
And so Jack
climbed the beanstalk.

136
00:06:57,644 --> 00:06:59,711
I want to see
everything!

137
00:06:59,744 --> 00:07:01,511
Come on,
bodyguards!

138
00:07:01,544 --> 00:07:02,878
Wait for me!

139
00:07:02,911 --> 00:07:08,144
Rocky road? Peanut brittle?
Chocolate fudge?

140
00:07:08,178 --> 00:07:11,311
[GIGGLING]

141
00:07:11,344 --> 00:07:13,778
Fedora?
Sunbonnet?

142
00:07:13,811 --> 00:07:17,144
How about something nice
for the young lady?

143
00:07:17,178 --> 00:07:19,278
Oh!
There you go!

144
00:07:25,244 --> 00:07:27,244
ABBY:
This city is amazing!

145
00:07:27,278 --> 00:07:28,544
I can't believe

146
00:07:28,578 --> 00:07:30,578
that robots are such
a normal part of daily life

147
00:07:30,611 --> 00:07:33,111
and people just accept them.

148
00:07:33,144 --> 00:07:35,811
That's because they know that
robots are here to help out.

149
00:07:35,844 --> 00:07:37,678
Does everyone
feel that way?

150
00:07:37,711 --> 00:07:39,378
Well, um--

151
00:07:39,411 --> 00:07:42,544
I'm afraid there are people like
Zaide here in the city too.

152
00:07:42,578 --> 00:07:45,711
Every place probably has
some people who hate robots.

153
00:07:45,744 --> 00:07:47,344
What a pity.

154
00:07:47,378 --> 00:07:49,844
But robots show more sense
than a lot of humans.

155
00:07:49,878 --> 00:07:51,811
They just keep doing
what they do,

156
00:07:51,844 --> 00:07:53,378
helping out
when they're needed,

157
00:07:53,411 --> 00:07:56,844
and trying to be useful
wherever they can.

158
00:07:56,878 --> 00:08:00,411
You put that nicely, Reno.

159
00:08:01,778 --> 00:08:03,878
[BOYS SNICKERING]

160
00:08:03,911 --> 00:08:06,711
Hey, what?
What's so funny?

161
00:08:06,744 --> 00:08:07,778
Nothing!

162
00:08:07,811 --> 00:08:09,611
What's
the big deal?

163
00:08:09,644 --> 00:08:12,344
N-n-nothing. Ignore them.
They're just kids.

164
00:08:12,378 --> 00:08:14,244
In case you hadn't
noticed, Reno--

165
00:08:14,278 --> 00:08:16,644
Put a lid
on it!

166
00:08:16,678 --> 00:08:19,644
I know, let's go
to the arena tomorrow!

167
00:08:19,678 --> 00:08:22,711
You haven't lived 'til you've
seen Harley play rocket ball!

168
00:08:22,744 --> 00:08:24,844
Oh, sounds like fun,

169
00:08:24,878 --> 00:08:26,833
but I'll be gone tomorrow.

170
00:08:26,867 --> 00:08:28,067
Huh?

171
00:08:28,100 --> 00:08:30,533
I must go home to Mayura.

172
00:08:30,567 --> 00:08:32,800
I'm expected
at a royal ceremony.

173
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:35,967
Oh.

174
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,000
Well, then,

175
00:08:37,033 --> 00:08:38,167
we've got to cram in

176
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:40,333
a whole week's
worth of fun right now!

177
00:08:40,367 --> 00:08:42,333
You leave tonight?
Yes.

178
00:08:42,367 --> 00:08:45,000
What time's
your shuttle?

179
00:08:45,033 --> 00:08:46,267
In three hours.

180
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:48,367
Then we've got
three whole hours!

181
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:50,967
There's lots of stuff
you can see in three hours.

182
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,500
Yeah,
Astro's right.

183
00:08:52,533 --> 00:08:56,333
Hey, let's take her to
the Marine Park to meet Jumbo!

184
00:08:56,367 --> 00:08:58,067
Or maybe we could all

185
00:08:58,100 --> 00:09:00,133
go ride the Whirl and Hurl
at Metro-Musements!

186
00:09:00,167 --> 00:09:01,167
You first!

187
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,233
[ALL LAUGHING]

188
00:09:02,267 --> 00:09:04,033
MAN:
Hold it right there!

189
00:09:04,067 --> 00:09:08,333
Princess Abby
is not going anywhere.

190
00:09:08,367 --> 00:09:11,233
[CHUCKLES]

191
00:09:19,067 --> 00:09:21,000
Fun's over, princess.

192
00:09:21,033 --> 00:09:22,133
Don't you
touch her!

193
00:09:22,167 --> 00:09:23,333
Why, you--

194
00:09:23,367 --> 00:09:24,533
ROBOT: Hats. Hats.
Huh?

195
00:09:24,567 --> 00:09:26,200
Wonderful hats!
Stop.

196
00:09:26,233 --> 00:09:27,000
How about you,
gentlemen?

197
00:09:27,033 --> 00:09:28,900
Quick!

198
00:09:28,933 --> 00:09:31,333
Show you our new spring line.
Out of my way!

199
00:09:31,367 --> 00:09:33,200
Ahhh!

200
00:09:33,233 --> 00:09:34,967
Wet floors.

201
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,300
Watch your step.

202
00:09:36,333 --> 00:09:38,133
Wet floors.

203
00:09:38,167 --> 00:09:40,400
Watch your step.

204
00:09:40,433 --> 00:09:41,833
Wet floors.
Stop them!

205
00:09:41,867 --> 00:09:44,067
Watch your step!

206
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:45,467
Wet floors.
Ahhh!

207
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:47,133
Watch your step.

208
00:09:47,167 --> 00:09:49,800
Wet floors.
Watch your step.

209
00:09:49,833 --> 00:09:52,000
Heh, heh!
Let's go!

210
00:09:52,033 --> 00:09:54,267
Grab those kids!

211
00:09:56,033 --> 00:09:57,933
Hurry, you guys!

212
00:09:59,067 --> 00:10:01,233
Abercrombie!

213
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:03,133
Grab onto me.

214
00:10:05,867 --> 00:10:06,933
Ohhh!

215
00:10:06,967 --> 00:10:08,167
Astro!

216
00:10:11,133 --> 00:10:14,033
Watch it, you--

217
00:10:14,067 --> 00:10:16,033
Astro,
you okay?

218
00:10:16,067 --> 00:10:17,167
Let me see.

219
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,867
He's going to be fine.

220
00:10:18,900 --> 00:10:20,967
Let me just patch up his servo.

221
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:22,200
There's no time.

222
00:10:22,233 --> 00:10:23,533
Get Abby out of here.

223
00:10:23,567 --> 00:10:25,467
In a minute.

224
00:10:26,967 --> 00:10:30,067
Ohhh.

225
00:10:30,100 --> 00:10:32,133
You'll be able
to walk now.

226
00:10:32,167 --> 00:10:34,867
But you're gonna have to forget
about flying for a while.

227
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:37,533
Thanks, Reno.

228
00:10:37,567 --> 00:10:39,433
Look out! Those guys are coming!

229
00:10:39,467 --> 00:10:40,933
ALL:
Huh?

230
00:10:40,967 --> 00:10:43,367
This is what they want.
The Scale of Tohron!

231
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:47,200
I won't allow any of you to
risk your lives for it anymore.

232
00:10:47,233 --> 00:10:49,467
ASTRO:
You can't do that, Abby!

233
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:51,967
Abby, you can give me
the Scale of Tohron.

234
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,200
You?

235
00:10:55,367 --> 00:10:57,967
There he is!
Ha-ha!

236
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,233
He's got the Scale!

237
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:04,000
Gotcha!

238
00:11:09,467 --> 00:11:10,467
[CHUCKLES]

239
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:12,500
I grew up in the Robot Circus!

240
00:11:12,533 --> 00:11:14,300
Try and catch--!

241
00:11:14,333 --> 00:11:18,867
Hey! Hey, let me go!
Let me go!

242
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:19,967
Reno!

243
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:24,267
Let go!

244
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:26,967
I want the Scale of Tohron.

245
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:30,000
You lose!
Because I don't have it.

246
00:11:30,033 --> 00:11:32,333
You worthless little insect!

247
00:11:32,367 --> 00:11:34,400
You will live to regret
defying Lord Zaide!

248
00:11:37,167 --> 00:11:39,000
ABBY:
We've got to save him!

249
00:11:39,033 --> 00:11:40,467
Take it easy, Abby.

250
00:11:40,500 --> 00:11:42,900
Right now we don't even
know where they've taken Reno.

251
00:11:42,933 --> 00:11:45,033
I think maybe
we should call the police.

252
00:11:45,067 --> 00:11:47,033
JODY: I have a ransom
message for Abby.

253
00:11:48,867 --> 00:11:49,833
Jody?

254
00:11:49,867 --> 00:11:51,800
Bring the Scale of Tohron

255
00:11:51,833 --> 00:11:55,500
to the top of the Bayside Bridge
tower at exactly 7:00.

256
00:11:55,533 --> 00:11:58,000
The boy in exchange
for the Scale.

257
00:11:58,033 --> 00:11:59,900
If you fail,
the boy will end up like me.

258
00:11:59,933 --> 00:12:01,567
Arggh!

259
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:05,467
ALL:
No! Jody!

260
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:08,533
Astro, is Jody--?
Is he, you know--?

261
00:12:08,567 --> 00:12:11,533
No, no worries.
It's just a short circuit.

262
00:12:11,567 --> 00:12:12,800
Reno can fix
him easily.

263
00:12:12,833 --> 00:12:14,967
ALL:
Phew.

264
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,467
TAWASHI:
Astro, there you are.

265
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:21,200
I need your help looking
for a missing person.

266
00:12:21,233 --> 00:12:22,900
This gentleman says
she's a princess.

267
00:12:22,933 --> 00:12:25,533
Hmm, well, she's about
your age and height and--

268
00:12:25,567 --> 00:12:26,867
Omar!

269
00:12:26,900 --> 00:12:28,000
[GASPS]

270
00:12:28,033 --> 00:12:29,333
Your Highness!

271
00:12:29,367 --> 00:12:31,433
Oh, Your Highness,
where have you been?

272
00:12:31,467 --> 00:12:33,167
I've been so worried.

273
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:35,000
I haven't slept!
I haven't eaten!

274
00:12:35,033 --> 00:12:36,833
If something were
to happen to you,

275
00:12:36,867 --> 00:12:38,533
I'd never be able
to look His Majesty

276
00:12:38,567 --> 00:12:40,200
in the eyes again.

277
00:12:40,233 --> 00:12:43,000
Forgive me, Omar.
I didn't mean to upset you.

278
00:12:43,033 --> 00:12:45,467
Who are these boys?

279
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:48,500
They're my friends. They've
been showing me Metro City.

280
00:12:48,533 --> 00:12:50,367
Oh, so that's it.

281
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:52,100
Really, princess,

282
00:12:52,133 --> 00:12:55,033
it's not that I condemn the
occasional youthful high jinks.

283
00:12:55,067 --> 00:12:59,200
Why, in my salad days, I myself
was quite the mischief maker.

284
00:12:59,233 --> 00:13:01,067
What happened
to this robot?

285
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:04,500
Uh, Jody, well, he, uh,
ran out of power just now.

286
00:13:04,533 --> 00:13:07,300
Well, you found
your princess.

287
00:13:07,333 --> 00:13:08,967
I guess this case
is closed.

288
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:09,867
Thank you, detective.

289
00:13:09,900 --> 00:13:12,000
Sorry to interrupt
your anniversary dinner.

290
00:13:12,033 --> 00:13:13,500
I'm just doing my job.

291
00:13:13,533 --> 00:13:15,233
Mrs. Tawashi understands.

292
00:13:15,267 --> 00:13:17,500
Crime never takes
a night off.

293
00:13:17,533 --> 00:13:19,367
ALL:
Phew.

294
00:13:21,433 --> 00:13:23,000
[RENO GROANS]

295
00:13:23,033 --> 00:13:24,233
It's no use.

296
00:13:27,333 --> 00:13:29,133
Abby.

297
00:13:32,433 --> 00:13:35,167
It's almost 7.
Time to head for the bridge.

298
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:38,800
And time for you to go home.
[GASPS]

299
00:13:38,833 --> 00:13:41,467
You have a duty to
the people of Mayura, Abby.

300
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:43,233
You are their inspiration,
their future,

301
00:13:43,267 --> 00:13:45,400
the Keeper
of the Scale of Tohron.

302
00:13:45,433 --> 00:13:47,300
That's why you must
go back to them.

303
00:13:47,333 --> 00:13:48,967
But--

304
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:51,833
It is as he says.
Please hurry, princess.

305
00:13:51,867 --> 00:13:53,467
If you're not at
the ceremony tomorrow,

306
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:55,167
you will disgrace your father

307
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:57,033
and bring shame
upon your family.

308
00:13:57,067 --> 00:13:59,300
You must leave
this other matter to Astro.

309
00:13:59,333 --> 00:14:02,500
Omar, Reno was captured
by Lord Zaide

310
00:14:02,533 --> 00:14:06,067
because he was only protecting
the Scale of Tohron for my sake.

311
00:14:06,100 --> 00:14:07,533
Well, perhaps, but--

312
00:14:07,567 --> 00:14:10,033
And now you're telling me
to simply abandon him,

313
00:14:10,067 --> 00:14:12,333
after all he's done?

314
00:14:12,367 --> 00:14:13,333
Well--

315
00:14:13,367 --> 00:14:16,333
If I leave him and run
back home to the Kingdom,

316
00:14:16,367 --> 00:14:18,900
how could I ever ask
my people for their trust?

317
00:14:18,933 --> 00:14:20,300
How can I wear
the Scale of Tohron,

318
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:23,133
knowing I betrayed a friend?

319
00:14:23,167 --> 00:14:24,967
I-- Ohhh.

320
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,333
ASTRO:
Abby.

321
00:14:26,367 --> 00:14:29,300
Astro, I'm going with you
to bring Reno back.

322
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:31,567
All right.

323
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:33,467
Promise me you'll do as I say.

324
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:35,300
Now let's go get Reno back!

325
00:14:49,967 --> 00:14:52,033
RENO: Give it up!
They're not coming!

326
00:14:52,067 --> 00:14:54,100
There's no way
Abby will ever

327
00:14:54,133 --> 00:14:56,133
hand over
the Scale of Tohron to you!

328
00:14:56,167 --> 00:14:58,433
Hmm. We'll see about that.

329
00:14:58,467 --> 00:15:00,067
ABBY: Reno!
Huh?

330
00:15:01,467 --> 00:15:02,533
Abby, no!

331
00:15:02,567 --> 00:15:04,033
Show me the Scale of Tohron.

332
00:15:04,067 --> 00:15:05,067
Don't do it!

333
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:10,267
Let him go.

334
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:12,933
Certainly, Your Highness.
Bring it over here.

335
00:15:12,967 --> 00:15:14,100
Stay back!

336
00:15:25,067 --> 00:15:27,100
Abby.

337
00:15:29,333 --> 00:15:31,567
Yes. This is it.

338
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:33,367
What are
you doing?

339
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:35,033
You double-crosser!

340
00:15:35,067 --> 00:15:38,000
Tomorrow the newspapers
will report

341
00:15:38,033 --> 00:15:40,067
that Princess Abby
and her friend are missing,

342
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:42,267
kidnapped by
renegade robots,

343
00:15:42,300 --> 00:15:44,400
and the grief-stricken
people of Mayura

344
00:15:44,433 --> 00:15:46,300
will overthrow
their robot-loving king

345
00:15:46,333 --> 00:15:48,000
and crown me their ruler.

346
00:15:48,033 --> 00:15:49,800
You will never be king!

347
00:15:49,833 --> 00:15:52,900
Sorry, princess. It seems
your plans fell through.

348
00:15:52,933 --> 00:15:55,100
ASTRO:
Got it!

349
00:15:55,133 --> 00:15:56,500
MAN:
Lord Zaide!

350
00:15:56,533 --> 00:15:57,800
Yes!

351
00:15:57,833 --> 00:15:59,267
Ugh!
Ah! Hah!

352
00:15:59,300 --> 00:16:00,933
Time to go!
What?

353
00:16:00,967 --> 00:16:05,267
Whooooaaaahhh!

354
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:09,467
I can't pedal fast enough,
Astro! Help!

355
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:11,267
Hang on!

356
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:12,533
BOTH:
Astro!

357
00:16:12,567 --> 00:16:14,500
Abby, catch!

358
00:16:16,567 --> 00:16:18,567
We're going down!

359
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:20,833
ALL:
Arrgh!

360
00:16:20,867 --> 00:16:23,133
ASTRO:
Ugh! Oh, hold on!

361
00:16:23,167 --> 00:16:24,800
All right!

362
00:16:24,833 --> 00:16:26,100
This is cool!

363
00:16:27,933 --> 00:16:29,867
That's it!

364
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:33,833
Over here, guys!

365
00:16:33,867 --> 00:16:35,067
Okay, ready!

366
00:16:35,100 --> 00:16:37,900
Kennedy, hi!
Alejo!

367
00:16:37,933 --> 00:16:40,267
ALL: Huh?
I've got you now!

368
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:42,233
Reno, Abby,
ready to jump!

369
00:16:42,267 --> 00:16:44,800
Ready!

370
00:16:44,833 --> 00:16:45,933
Whoa!

371
00:16:45,967 --> 00:16:48,867
Perfect! Whoa!

372
00:16:48,900 --> 00:16:50,133
Abercrombie,
hang on tight!

373
00:16:50,167 --> 00:16:51,167
Gotcha!

374
00:16:54,367 --> 00:16:55,433
Whoa!

375
00:16:55,467 --> 00:16:57,367
ASTRO:
Hey!

376
00:16:57,400 --> 00:17:00,100
You meddlers!

377
00:17:00,133 --> 00:17:01,833
Abercrombie, take over!

378
00:17:05,167 --> 00:17:07,233
Blast him! Shake him off!

379
00:17:07,267 --> 00:17:09,300
Right!
Whoa!

380
00:17:13,267 --> 00:17:16,400
I'm so glad you were able
to finish up your work, dear.

381
00:17:16,433 --> 00:17:18,567
After all,
it is our anniversary.

382
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:21,100
It's nice to have
one night a year

383
00:17:21,133 --> 00:17:23,533
without emergencies
or flying robots.

384
00:17:23,567 --> 00:17:24,533
[SIGHS]

385
00:17:27,267 --> 00:17:29,833
Ugh! Ugh! Arrgh!

386
00:17:29,867 --> 00:17:31,133
ZAIDE:
Finish them off!

387
00:17:31,167 --> 00:17:33,067
Yes, sir!

388
00:17:33,100 --> 00:17:34,400
Head for the airport!

389
00:17:37,967 --> 00:17:40,233
RENO:
We're almost at the airport.

390
00:17:40,267 --> 00:17:42,200
We'll use this
to get there.

391
00:17:42,233 --> 00:17:43,267
Well,
what is it?

392
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:46,233
A Quadra-glider. Kind of
like a four-man flying bike.

393
00:17:46,267 --> 00:17:49,233
KENNEDY:
We'll get you to the airport
in no time.

394
00:17:49,267 --> 00:17:51,067
ABBY:
Look! How beautiful!

395
00:17:51,100 --> 00:17:52,033
ALEJO:
Let's do it!

396
00:18:02,067 --> 00:18:04,000
Wow!

397
00:18:05,567 --> 00:18:08,300
ALL:
Huh?

398
00:18:08,333 --> 00:18:10,567
Abby, give me
the Scale of Tohron!

399
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:12,967
Now!

400
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:15,967
Or I'll take care of you
one at a time.

401
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:18,267
Starting with
the one on the end!

402
00:18:18,300 --> 00:18:19,300
Argh!

403
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:21,867
ALL:
Astro!

404
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:24,367
Take down that robot now!

405
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:30,067
Arrgh!

406
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:31,300
[LAUGHS]

407
00:18:32,333 --> 00:18:34,400
RENO:
Astro, over here!

408
00:18:34,433 --> 00:18:35,233
Ugh! Ugh!

409
00:18:38,833 --> 00:18:42,067
[ALL STRAINING & GASPING]

410
00:18:42,100 --> 00:18:44,333
That's enough! The game is over!

411
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:48,567
Arrgh! What's happening?

412
00:18:48,600 --> 00:18:50,067
ALL:
Ohh.

413
00:18:52,133 --> 00:18:54,254
TAWASHI:
I don't know what's going on,

414
00:18:54,287 --> 00:18:56,220
but this better be
the bad guy.

415
00:18:56,254 --> 00:18:57,487
Hey, guys!

416
00:18:57,520 --> 00:18:59,054
Abercrombie!
Detective!

417
00:18:59,087 --> 00:19:00,854
Are we glad
to see you!

418
00:19:05,754 --> 00:19:06,954
Your Highness!

419
00:19:10,054 --> 00:19:12,720
Look down there!
It's Omar!

420
00:19:12,754 --> 00:19:15,220
ABBY: Hey, Omar!
OMAR: Your Highness!

421
00:19:15,254 --> 00:19:17,820
Well, looks like
you made it.

422
00:19:17,854 --> 00:19:19,554
Just in time.

423
00:19:19,587 --> 00:19:21,020
We're coming in!

424
00:19:26,287 --> 00:19:27,920
[CHUCKLING]

425
00:19:27,954 --> 00:19:30,954
Your Highness, thank goodness
you're safe and sound.

426
00:19:30,987 --> 00:19:34,954
What is that?
You couldn't take a cab?

427
00:19:34,987 --> 00:19:36,087
Abby, it's been
a blast!

428
00:19:36,120 --> 00:19:36,987
Come back soon!

429
00:19:44,620 --> 00:19:46,587
OMAR:
Ahem, Your Highness, please,

430
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:48,554
we must go.

431
00:19:48,587 --> 00:19:51,120
Well, come on. Come on,
say something, Reno.

432
00:19:51,154 --> 00:19:53,154
She's leaving.
Go on, Reno.

433
00:19:53,187 --> 00:19:54,820
Reno?

434
00:19:58,254 --> 00:20:01,720
Your Highness,
we really must be going.

435
00:20:02,854 --> 00:20:05,820
RENO: Uh, wait, Abby.

436
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:08,154
Here.

437
00:20:20,020 --> 00:20:21,820
Thank you.

438
00:20:21,854 --> 00:20:23,854
Reno, promise
you won't forget about me.

439
00:20:23,887 --> 00:20:25,487
Of course not.

440
00:20:31,054 --> 00:20:34,020
[ALL LAUGHING]

441
00:20:34,054 --> 00:20:36,954
ALL: Bye! So long!
See you soon!

442
00:20:40,654 --> 00:20:42,587
[♪]

